All Implemented Interfaces:
Appender, Filterable, LifeCycle
@Configurable(elementType="appender", printObject=true) @Plugin("NoSql") public final class NoSqlAppender extends AbstractDatabaseAppender<NoSqlDatabaseManager<?>>
This Appender writes logging events to a NoSQL database using a configured NoSQL provider. It requires implementations of NoSqlObject, NoSqlConnection, and NoSqlProvider to "know" how to write events to the chosen NoSQL database.

For examples on how to write your own NoSQL provider, see the simple source code for the MongoDB providers.
